definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  2-phospho-D-glycerate -eq- phosphoenolpyruvate + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  1-(5-phosphonatoribosyl)-5'-AMP + H(2)O -eq- 1-(5-phosphoribosyl)-5-[(5-phosphoribosylamino)methylideneamino]imidazole-4-carboxamide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  1-(5-phospho-D-ribosyl)-ATP + H(2)O -eq- 1-(5-phosphonatoribosyl)-5'-AMP + diphosphate + H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  5-phospho-D-ribosylamine + ATP + glycine -eq- N(1)-(5-phospho-D-ribosyl)glycinamide + ADP + 2 H(+) + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  5-amino-1-(5-phospho-D-ribosyl)imidazole-4-carboxylate + 2 H(+) -eq- 5-amino-1-(5-phospho-D-ribosyl)imidazole + CO(2).

Catalysis of the reaction -  5-amino-1-(5-phospho-D-ribosyl)imidazole-4-carboxylate + L-aspartate + ATP -eq- (2S)-2-[5-amino-1-(5-phospho-beta-D-ribosyl)imidazole-4-carboxamido]succinate + ADP + 2 H(+) + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N-(5-phospho-beta-D-ribosyl)anthranilate -eq- 1-(2-carboxyphenylamino)-1-deoxy-D-ribulose 5-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-(formamido)-N(1)-(5-phospho-D-ribosyl)acetamidine + ATP -eq- 5-amino-1-(5-phospho-D-ribosyl)imidazole + ADP + 2 H(+) + phosphate.

Catalysis of the reaction -  N(2)-formyl-N(1)-(5-phospho-D-ribosyl)glycinamide + L-glutamine + ATP + H(2)O -eq- 2-(formamido)-N(1)-(5-phospho-D-ribosyl)acetamidine + L-glutamate + ADP + 2 H(+) + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  10-formyltetrahydrofolate + 5'-phosphoribosyl-5-amino-4-imidazolecarboxamide -eq- tetrahydrofolate + 5'-phosphoribosyl-5-formamido-4-imidazolecarboxamide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  10-formyltetrahydrofolate + N1-(5-phospho-D-ribosyl)glycinamide -eq- tetrahydrofolate + N2-formyl-N1-(5-phospho-D-ribosyl)glycinamide.

Catalysis of the reaction -  1,4-alpha-D-glucosyl(n) + phosphate -eq- 1,4-alpha-D-glucosyl(n-1) + alpha-D-glucose 1-phosphate. The name should be qualified in each instance by adding the name of the natural substrate, e.g. maltodextrin phosphorylase, starch phosphorylase, glycogen phosphorylase.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L(or D)-O-phosphoserine + H2O -eq- L(or D)-serine + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  O-phospho-L-serine + 2-oxoglutarate -eq- 3-phosphonooxypyruvate + L-glutamate.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of poly(ADP-ribose) at glycosidic (1''-2') linkage of ribose-ribose bond to produce free ADP-ribose.
Catalysis of the random hydrolysis of (1--gt-4)-alpha-D-galactosiduronic linkages in pectate and other galacturonans.
Catalysis of the reaction -  5'-phosphopolynucleotide + H2O -eq- polynucleotide + phosphate.

Catalysis of the template-independent extension of the 3'- end of an RNA or DNA strand by addition of one adenosine molecule at a time. Cannot initiate a chain 'de novo'. The primer, depending on the source of the enzyme, may be an RNA or DNA fragment, or oligo(A) bearing a 3'-OH terminal group.

Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-N-acetyl-D-galactosamine + polypeptide -eq- UDP + N-acetyl-D-galactosaminyl-polypeptide. This reaction is the modification of serine or threonine residues in polypeptide chains by the transfer of a N-acetylgalactose from UDP-N-acetylgalactose to the hydroxyl group of the amino acid -  it is the first step in O-glycan biosynthesis.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + RNA(n) -eq- diphosphate + RNA(n+1).
Catalysis of the reaction -  2 5-aminolevulinate -eq- 2 H(2)O + H(+) + porphobilinogen.
Catalysis of the reaction -  procollagen L-proline + 2-oxoglutarate + O2 -eq- procollagen trans-4-hydroxy-L-proline + succinate + CO2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-proline + acceptor -eq- (S)-1-pyrroline-5-carboxylate + reduced acceptor.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + propanoyl-CoA + HCO3- -eq- ADP + phosphate + (S)-methylmalonyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the transfer of a prenyl group from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor).
Catalysis of the reaction -  farnesyl diphosphate + protein-cysteine -eq- S-farnesyl protein + diphosphate.
Catalysis of the covalent addition of a geranylgeranyl (20-carbon isoprenoid) group via thioether linkages to a cysteine residue at or near the C terminus of a protein.

Catalysis of the reaction -  geranylgeranyl diphosphate + protein-cysteine -eq- S-geranylgeranyl-protein + diphosphate. This reaction is the formation of a thioether linkage between the C-1 atom of the geranylgeranyl group and a cysteine residue fourth from the C-terminus of the protein. The protein substrates have the C-terminal sequence CA1A2X, where the terminal residue, X, is preferably leucine and A2 should not be aromatic. Known substrates include most g-subunits of heterotrimeric G proteins and Ras-related GTPases such as members of the Ras and Rac|Rho families.

Catalysis of the reaction -  2 geranylgeranyl diphosphate + protein-cysteine -eq- 2 S-geranylgeranyl-protein + 2 diphosphate. This reaction is the formation of two thioether linkages between the C-1 atom of the geranylgeranyl groups and two cysteine residues within the terminal sequence motifs XXCC, XCXC or CCXX. Known substrates include Ras-related GTPases of a single family and the Rab family.
Catalysis of the reaction -  prephenate -eq- phenylpyruvate + H2O + CO2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  NADP(+) + prephenate -eq- (4-hydroxyphenyl)pyruvate + CO(2) + NADPH.
Catalysis of the reaction -  arachidonate + donor-H2 + 2 O2 -eq- prostaglandin H2 + acceptor + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  prostaglandin H(2) -eq- prostaglandin D(2).
Catalysis of the reaction -  protein L-arginine + H2O -eq- protein L-citrulline + NH3.

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + protein C-terminal S-farnesyl-L-cysteine -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + protein C-terminal S-farnesyl-L-cysteine methyl ester.
Catalysis of the phosphorylation of an amino acid residue in a protein, usually according to the reaction -  a protein + ATP -eq- a phosphoprotein + ADP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + protein L-histidine -eq- ADP + protein phospho-L-histidine.
Catalysis of the reactions -  ATP + protein serine -eq- ADP + protein serine phosphate, and ATP + protein threonine -eq- ADP + protein threonine phosphate.

label.value: transmembrane receptor protein serine|threonine kinase activity

definition.value: Combining with a signal and transmitting the signal from one side of the membrane to the other to initiate a change in cell activity by catalysis of the reaction -  ATP protein serine -eq- ADP + protein serine phosphate, and ATP + protein threonine -eq- ADP + protein threonine phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + a protein -eq- ADP + a phosphoprotein. This reaction requires the presence of a phosphatidylinositol-3-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + a protein -eq- ADP + a phosphoprotein. This reaction requires the presence of DNA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + a protein -eq- ADP + a phosphoprotein. This reaction requires the presence of AMP.

Catalysis of the reactions -  ATP + a protein serine -eq- ADP + protein serine phosphate -  and ATP + a protein threonine -eq- ADP + protein threonine phosphate. These reactions require the presence of calcium-bound calmodulin.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + [elongation factor 2] -eq- ADP + [elongation factor 2] phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + myosin-light-chain -eq- ADP + myosin-light-chain phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  4 ATP + 2 phosphorylase b -eq- 4 ADP + phosphorylase a.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + a protein -eq- ADP + a phosphoprotein. This reaction requires the presence of a cyclic nucleotide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + a protein -eq- ADP + a phosphoprotein. This reaction requires the presence of cAMP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + a protein -eq- ADP + a phosphoprotein. This reaction requires the presence of cGMP.

Catalysis of the reactions -  ATP + protein serine -eq- ADP + protein serine phosphate, and ATP + protein threonine -eq- ADP + protein threonine phosphate. This reaction requires the binding of a regulatory cyclin subunit and full activity requires stimulatory phosphorylation by a CDK-activating kinase (CAK).
